Agent-Based Models and Sustainability

Ernesto Carrella

May 22, 2018

Why bother ?

  • Details
  • Model flexibility is fundamental for good policy analysis
  • Computational models are more flexible

An academic example

  • Marine reserves solve an important bycatch problem in fisheries, PNAS, 2017
  • Assume that:
    • There are only 2 species of fish
    • Sea soup distribution
    • Manager perfectly observes biomass
    • Fishers exploit optimally
  • Then:
    • We can prove mathematically that protected areas are better than constant escapement rules

Questions that actually get asked

  • In a 81-species complex, who wins and loses after a price shock?
  • How to police a segment of the fishery given that another set of boats cannot be regulated?
  • How to rotate protected areas in a fair manner?
  • What happens to fishing efficiency once we switch from one policy to another?

Not an easy fix

  • Curse of dimensionality : finding the optimal fishing path is often mathematically intractable
  • Deep uncertainty
